The Fox News host Steve Hilton called it "fascistic" and a "no-child policy."
For some would-be parents, climate change is a consideration.
Hilton and others on the network said the 29-year-old lawmaker is demanding that Americans stop having children and submit to "civilizational suicide."
"She's saying, 'don't have kids' because it's going to hurt our country," "Fox & Friends" host Pete Hegseth said on Tuesday.
"So if you don't believe in kids, and families, and the flag, then you're effectively admitting to civilizational suicide."